Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.68,0:03:28.60,Title Cards2,,0,0,0,,{\blur1.5}{\pos(358.576,666.25)}{\fs70}EPISODE 21\N{\fs90}NERV IS BORN
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.60,0:03:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Abducted?! The Vice Commander?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.35,0:03:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened two hours ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.44,0:03:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He was last seen in District 8 on the west side.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.61,0:03:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s within our compound!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.48,0:03:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What was your Intelligence Department doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.78,0:03:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s an insider who leaked information\Nand instigated this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.03,0:03:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He was able to get the better of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.08,0:03:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone who can pull the wool over\Nthe eyes of Intelligence Division 2?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.79,0:03:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It can’t be!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.45,0:03:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryoji Kaji is the man believed to be\Nthe mastermind behind this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.21,0:03:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s why you’re here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.88,0:03:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We appreciate your quick understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.26,0:04:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,As a member of the same organization,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.13,0:04:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,it is regrettable that we must suspect\Nthe Chief of Operations,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.01,0:04:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but this is part of our job.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.89,0:04:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Considering the history between me and him,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.26,0:04:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it seems like the logical step to take.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.31,0:04:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.98,0:04:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Take her away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.65,0:04:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It has been a while, Chairman Kiel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.65,0:04:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This is quite a rude welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.32,0:04:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I need not apologize to you for the impropriety.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.44,0:04:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a necessary procedure in order\Nto speak with you at leisure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.37,0:04:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You certainly haven’t changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.16,0:04:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Does my convenience mean nothing then?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.70,0:04:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem being discussed\Nis an urgent matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.50,0:04:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It was unavoidable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.12,0:04:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Please understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.00,0:04:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it’s Seele and not the Committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.21,0:04:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no intention of creating a new god.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.55,0:04:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We would like your cooperation,\NProfessor Fuyutsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.22,0:04:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Fuyutsuki…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.56,0:04:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor! Professor Fuyutsuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.31,0:04:52.77,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs90\pos(960,335)\3c&H8E8E8E&}YEAR 1999, KYOTO
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.02,0:04:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it’s you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.69,0:04:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You wanna join us for some beer in Kamogawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.40,0:05:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Again?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.61,0:05:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryoko and the others are saying\Nthey’ll go if you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.19,0:05:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Our professor was also saying you should\Nshow up once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.36,0:05:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.20,0:05:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s good to go out and have\Na drink every so often.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.16,0:05:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.25,0:05:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You excel at your work,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.87,0:05:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but you don’t take socializing seriously\Nand that’s not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.38,0:05:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure you’re right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.88,0:05:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, Fuyutsuki,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.76,0:05:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s a bioengineering student\Nwho submitted an interesting paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.43,0:05:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The student’s name is Ikari. Do you know her?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.47,0:05:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Ikari? No, I don’t.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.81,0:05:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I told her about you and she said\Nshe was interested in meeting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.44,0:05:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,She’ll probably contact you eventually,\Nso take care of things, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.06,0:05:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Ikari, was it? All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.27,0:05:43.86,Neutral Sign,,0,0,0,,{\frz1.398\c&H000014&\pos(953.333,304.334)}Metaphysical Biology Research Room 1 Fuyutsuki
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.53,0:05:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I read your paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.57,0:05:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I found a couple of things questionable,\Nbut it was a stimulating paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.07,0:05:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.58,0:05:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yui Ikari, wasn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.04,0:05:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.12,0:05:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What are your plans for the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.00,0:05:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to find work?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.25,0:06:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Or do you intend to join the research lab here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.25,0:06:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven’t thought that far ahead yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.63,0:06:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And besides, aren’t you forgetting a third option?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.30,0:06:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m also considering a domestic life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.30,0:06:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, that’s only if I can find someone nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.02,0:06:16.31,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs90\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,361.667)}BACK IN THE YEAR 2015
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.77,0:06:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,With an S2 engine on board,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.81,0:06:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Evangelion Unit 01 has become\Nan absolute being!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.02,0:06:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no use for an actualized god.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.40,0:06:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We must not create a god.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.82,0:06:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We cannot allow that man to create a god.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.33,0:06:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Gendo Ikari, is he a man that can be trusted?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.37,0:06:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Gendo Rokubungi? I’ve heard of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.08,0:06:42.88,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs90\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,357.667)}BACK IN THE YEAR 1999
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.00,0:06:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I’ve never met him,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.54,0:06:50.43,Signs,,0,0,0,,Kyoto Prefecture Police Department
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.71,0:06:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but there’s always some rumor\Ngoing around about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.01,0:06:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What? He asked to be released\Ninto my custody?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.88,0:06:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I’ll come.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.47,0:06:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,When should I come over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.22,0:06:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard about you from a certain person,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.93,0:07:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,so I wanted to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.06,0:07:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re a rather coarse man,\Nto get into a drunken brawl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.40,0:07:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no time to talk.\NThey just picked a fight with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.53,0:07:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not very good at being liked,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.65,0:07:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,but I am used to being treated coldly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.20,0:07:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it’s none of my business anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.95,0:07:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Fuyutsuki,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.50,0:07:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you seem to be exactly the person\NI expected you to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.88,0:07:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, my first impression of him was of distaste.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.42,0:07:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And back then, seasons and autumn\Nstill existed in this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.13,0:07:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.39,0:07:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I am seeing Mr. Rokubungi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.14,0:07:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,When I heard that, I wasn’t able\Nto hide my surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.31,0:07:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I never would have thought you would\Nshare your time with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.11,0:07:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but Professor Fuyutsuki,\Nhe’s quite a sweet person.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.90,0:07:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just that no one knows it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.82,0:07:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it’s more blissful not to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.95,0:07:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I inconvenience you by\Nintroducing you to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.08,0:08:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I’ll admit that he’s an interesting man,\Nthough I can’t get to like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.00,0:08:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But within our circle, the common opinion\Nwas that he had approached Yui
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.63,0:08:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,for her talent and for\Nthe organization backing her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.92,0:08:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, I would hear rumors that this\Norganization was called Seele.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.43,0:08:17.89,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs90\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,347)}YEAR 2000, ANTARCTICA
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.68,0:08:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The Second Impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.39,0:08:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That tragedy occurred in the final year\Nof the 20th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.10,0:08:30.57,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs90\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,356.333)}YEAR 2001
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.77,0:08:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And the first year of the 21st century\Nwas pure hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.23,0:08:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no other word to describe that year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.61,0:08:31.44,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs90\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,356.333)}YEAR 2002
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.49,0:08:32.95,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs50\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,377.667)}RUINS OF TOYOHASHI CITY, AICHI PREFECTURE
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.12,0:08:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear temperatures will rise above\N30 degrees Celsius again today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.45,0:08:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It certainly is hot over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.87,0:08:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That isn’t even rare in Japan these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.54,0:08:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Summer has lasted for almost a year now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.17,0:08:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s rough on the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.00,0:08:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t want to move to that ship up there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.59,0:08:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean the next town over?\NThat place constantly stinks of oil.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.09,0:08:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can’t get to like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.80,0:09:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, I never imagined you’d\Nset up shop in such a place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.56,0:09:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a lot of trouble finding you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.02,0:09:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re short on doctors here,\Nlike everywhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.27,0:09:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a mockery, but it’s better than nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.03,0:09:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Going to Antarctica at this late date?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.53,0:09:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a formal investigation of the incident\Ncommissioned by the UN Council.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.70,0:09:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a provisional organization,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.83,0:09:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but I would think you could be of\Nmore use to the world there,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.45,0:09:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,than working as an unlicensed doctor here,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.21,0:09:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Fuyutsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.92,0:09:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s “former professor”.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.88,0:09:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, my column is blank.\NWho recommended me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.63,0:09:35.34,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs90\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,352.333)}SAME YEAR, ANTARCTICA
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.34,0:09:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,To think this was once a continent of ice…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.43,0:09:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no trace of it left.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.31,0:09:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Fuyutsuki…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.52,0:09:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.81,0:09:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m surprised you survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.77,0:09:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d heard that you were a member\Nof the Katsuragi Research Team.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.61,0:09:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Luckily, I had returned to Japan\Nthe day before the incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.65,0:09:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,so I was able to escape the tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.61,0:09:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.20,0:10:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Rokubungi, you…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.62,0:10:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, I have a different name now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.04,0:10:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A postcard? Not a business card?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.25,0:10:08.67,Sloppy Sign,,0,0,0,,{\frz341\c&H000009&\pos(907.44,294)}We’re Married
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.25,0:10:08.67,Sloppy Sign,,0,0,0,,{\frz341\c&H000009&\pos(1180.469,390.166)}Gendo & Yui\NIkari
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.25,0:10:08.67,Sloppy Sign,,0,0,0,,{\frz341\c&H000009&\pos(1078.44,702)}It has been\Na long time.\NAre you doing well?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.54,0:10:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Ikari? Gendo Ikari…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.13,0:10:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife has been nagging me to get\Nthis to you, Professor Fuyutsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.67,0:10:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,She seems to be a fan of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.67,0:10:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m honored.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.72,0:10:22.97,Sloppy Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H000009&\frz332\fs80\pos(1552.711,-2.75)}Gendo & Yui\NIkari
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.72,0:10:22.97,Sloppy Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H000009&\frz331.7\fs80\pos(1270.576,408.583)}It has been\Na long time.\NAre you doing well?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.55,0:10:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,How is Yui doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.30,0:10:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t she participating in this expedition?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.51,0:10:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yui wanted to come, but we\Nhave a child now, so…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.48,0:10:37.15,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\frz353\c&H000000&\3c&H0894A5&\fs55\pos(650.773,465.168)}SAFETY FIRST
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.02,0:10:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Your organization… Seele, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.19,0:10:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve heard nothing but bad things about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.11,0:10:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t approve of forcibly pinning down\Nthe board of directors.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.82,0:10:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re fastidious as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.95,0:10:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,No clean organization can survive\Nin this day and age anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.33,0:10:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The official investigation of the Second Impact…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.24,0:10:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If the investigation team consisted\Nonly of Seele people,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.46,0:10:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you would run into all sorts of issues later.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.88,0:10:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re just a makeshift solution\Nto avoid that, aren’t we?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.46,0:10:57.42,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs90\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,347)}YEAR 2015
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.46,0:10:59.72,Signs,,0,0,0,,Nerv Headquarters - Isolation Facility 4
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.18,0:11:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I still don’t handle dark places very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.68,0:11:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All the bad memories come flooding back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.43,0:11:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.64,0:11:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s the sole survivor of the original expedition.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.98,0:11:09.94,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs90\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,347)}YEAR 2002
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.94,0:11:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Her name is Misato Katsuragi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.98,0:11:12.94,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs50\c&H834B40&\pos(960,65.667)}SOUTH POLE INVESTIGATION SHIP - ISOLATION FACILITY 2
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.35,0:11:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Katsuragi? She’s Dr. Katsuragi’s daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.32,0:11:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, she hasn’t spoken for\Nalmost two years now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.99,0:11:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.28,0:11:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It attests to the hell that she witnessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.41,0:11:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Her physical injuries have healed,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.07,0:11:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but psychological wounds do not heal so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.62,0:11:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.16,0:11:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We can’t conclude our findings for our\Ninvestigation lightly either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.04,0:11:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,A completely localized change to\Nthe atmospheric elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.67,0:11:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The thorough extermination of all life,\Nincluding microorganisms.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.34,0:11:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The traces of an enormous cavern\Ndirectly below the blast center.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.68,0:11:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And this giant of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.47,0:11:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This incident is full of mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.06,0:11:54.90,Neutral Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord4\pos(960,336.6)\c&H000000&\3c&HDDDBD6&\fs60}United Nations Moves Headquarters to Japan\NIn Five Years, Candidate is New Tokyo-2\NSecond Impact Caused by a Massive Meteor\NImpossible to Predict or Avoid\NProbability of Once in Every Several\NHundred Million Years\NOfficial United Nations Statement\NAt 20-30% of the Speed of Light
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.52,0:11:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon after, the United Nations issued\Nan official statement
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.10,0:11:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,stating that the Second lmpact was\Ncaused by a massive meteor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.27,0:11:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But from where I stood, I could see
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.23,0:12:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that the information had been\Nblatantly massaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.49,0:12:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Behind all this was Seele and hints that\Na man named Kiel was involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.66,0:12:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And it made me want to learn the\Ndark truth of that incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.75,0:12:12.08,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs90\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,336.333)}YEAR 2003, HAKONE
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.95,0:12:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if that might eventually lead me\Nto the name of Yui Ikari.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.08,0:12:14.21,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs50\bord2\c&HF3D4DE&\pos(960,765.667)}UNITED NATIONS ARTIFICIAL EVOLUTION LABORATORY
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.51,0:12:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It has been a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.05,0:12:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it has.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.27,0:12:35.81,Signs,,0,0,0,,{{\bord2\blur1.5\fs80\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,112.333)\frz359.5}DIRECTOR’S OFFICE
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.35,0:12:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you hide the existence\Nof the giant of light?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.86,0:12:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys knew about the\NSecond Impact, didn’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.61,0:12:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That it would happen on that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.28,0:12:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You said you were lucky enough\Nto get out the day before.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.50,0:12:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it also luck that you took\Nall your research with you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.08,0:13:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I am surprised that this material\Nescaped destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.96,0:13:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I did a thorough investigation of your assets.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.63,0:13:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure raising a child is expensive,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.18,0:13:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,but isn’t the amount rather large\Nfor you to have privately?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.22,0:13:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You impress me, Professor Fuyutsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.22,0:13:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not transfer to the department\Nof economics?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.81,0:13:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to go public about Seele\Nand the Dead Sea Scrolls
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.15,0:13:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,being secretly behind the Second Impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.61,0:13:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no intention of letting the people\Nwho caused that get away with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.49,0:13:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Feel free.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.78,0:13:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But before you do, there is something\NI would like to show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.28,0:13:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re going down quite a ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.29,0:13:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it worry you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.83,0:13:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Somewhat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.17,0:13:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.21,0:13:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A cavern left behind by someone,\Nwho was not us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.46,0:13:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Though eighty-nine percent of it is buried.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.34,0:13:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,An underground cavern that was originally\Na neat spherical shape…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.43,0:13:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this the same as the underground\Ncavern found at the South Pole?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.06,0:13:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The data from them are virtually identical.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.85,0:13:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you intend to repeat\Nthat tragedy once again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.81,0:14:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that what you’re doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.65,0:14:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether we are or not, please\Ndetermine that for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.36,0:14:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All the resources mankind has to offer\Nare being poured into that facility.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.62,0:14:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Professor Fuyutsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.17,0:14:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi, you too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.38,0:14:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is the best place to research
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.50,0:14:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the fundamental theories for the\Nbio-computers of the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.51,0:14:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.84,0:14:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I intend to name it Magi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.72,0:14:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Magi? After the three wise men from the East?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.06,0:14:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this what you wanted to show me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.22,0:14:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No, this way, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.94,0:14:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Ritsuko, I’ll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.52,0:14:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.94,0:14:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this that giant?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.49,0:14:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Here at Gehirn, we call that giant Adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.86,0:14:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.41,0:14:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not the original.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.66,0:14:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Then…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.49,0:15:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it is an Eva, made from Adam by man.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.67,0:15:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,An Eva?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.96,0:15:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Adam Revival Project,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.29,0:15:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,generally known as Project E,\Nand this is our mockup,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.67,0:15:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva Unit 00.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.72,0:15:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A prototype for a god?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.68,0:15:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Fuyutsuki,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.01,0:15:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,work with me to create a new era\Nin the history of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.06,0:15:21.98,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs90\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,347)}YEAR 2015
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.40,0:15:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, Ma’am?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.40,0:15:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I’m sorry. Let’s hurry up and retest Rei.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.94,0:15:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven’t seen Miss Katsuragi around today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.82,0:15:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.78,0:15:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Katsuragi?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.03,0:15:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Right! Misato Katsuragi! Nice to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.20,0:15:39.16,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs80\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,172.333)}YEAR 2005\NNEW TOKYO-2, NAGANO PREFECTURE
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.75,0:15:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.25,0:15:42.67,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs60\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,400.333)}2ND TOKYO UNIVERSITY, SCHOOL GROUNDS
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.21,0:15:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I met a girl named Katsuragi the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.17,0:15:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people will only look at me from afar,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.84,0:15:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and each time, I am reminded of\Nthe weight your name carries,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.34,0:15:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but this girl has no reservation\Ntowards me for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.14,0:15:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I am told that she is the sole survivor\Nof that expedition.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.93,0:16:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,She was apparently aphasic for a time,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.18,0:16:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but now, she chatters away a mile a minute\Nas if to make up for lost time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.06,0:16:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ritchan, I am still burrowed underground,\Nthe same as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.32,0:16:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve grown tired of the lunches they provide.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.03,0:16:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,On the surface, they have apparently begun\Nworking on the plans for New Tokyo-3
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.20,0:16:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in accordance with the Second\NCapital Transfer Project.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.08,0:16:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Lately, Misato hadn’t been showing up\Nat the university,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.66,0:16:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and when I finally got her to tell me why,\Nit was so idiotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.62,0:16:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently, she had been sleeping with\Nher boyfriend at her apartment,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.79,0:16:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for an entire week!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.92,0:16:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like I have seen an unexpected side of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.34,0:16:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,She introduced him to me today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.34,0:16:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s good-looking,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.76,0:16:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but I just cannot get to like his frivolous attitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.60,0:16:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,As I recall, you have never been\Ngood around boys, Ritchan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.14,0:16:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, being raised only by a woman…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.56,0:16:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I’m sorry. I have left you to your\Nown devices for so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.15,0:16:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s awful of me to act like a mother\Nonly when it’s convenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.49,0:16:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,A mother…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.45,0:16:57.41,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs90\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,347)}YEAR 2003
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.45,0:16:58.41,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs90\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,347)}ASHINOKO LAKEFRONT, HAKONE
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.45,0:17:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Today is just like every other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.20,0:17:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The disappearance of autumn\Nfrom this country is truly sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.12,0:17:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The secret Dead Sea Scrolls\Nthat Seele possesses…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.21,0:17:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If things happen as it is written in those scrolls,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.00,0:17:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the Third Impact will happen in\Nanother decade or so without fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.01,0:17:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The organizations are meant\Nto prevent the final tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.26,0:17:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That is what Seele and Gehirn are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.22,0:17:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I support your ideas, not Seele’s.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.64,0:17:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Fuyutsuki, it will be very dangerous\Nto unleash that seal upon the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.23,0:17:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I have already handed the data over to Ikari.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.23,0:17:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not something that can be accomplished\Nby an individual after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.99,0:17:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There won’t be a repeat performance\Nof the stunt I pulled earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.62,0:17:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’ve sort of received a warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.46,0:17:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting rid of me couldn’t be easier\Nfor them, it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.88,0:17:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The same goes for all the survivors.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.17,0:17:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a simple thing to destroy people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.80,0:17:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But that’s no reason for you to become\Nan experimental subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.59,0:18:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I will go along with the flow of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.81,0:18:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, that is why I am at Seele.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.27,0:18:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,For Shinji.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.86,0:18:20.82,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs90\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,347)}YEAR 2004
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.91,0:18:22.24,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs70\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,365.667)}HAKONE - UNDERGROUND LABORATORY 2
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.78,0:18:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,LCL electrified. Pressure at plus zero point two.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.33,0:18:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,No destrudo readings detected in transmissions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.41,0:18:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Para-base is stable.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.50,0:18:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this child doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.71,0:18:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s Director Ikari’s son.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.00,0:18:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ikari, this is not a nursery school.\NToday is a crucial day!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.30,0:18:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry, Professor Fuyutsuki.\NI’m the one who brought him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.97,0:18:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yui, this is your experiment today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.14,0:18:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.56,0:18:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to show my child the bright future.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.06,0:18:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Those were Ms. Yui’s final words.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.02,0:18:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The irregular circumstances erased her\Nfrom this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.61,0:18:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly as I had wished.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.82,0:19:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I am such a horrible woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.95,0:19:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Ritchan, Director Ikari changed after that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.29,0:19:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Where have you been for the past week?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.79,0:19:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re allowed to grieve, but you\Nneed to be aware
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.58,0:19:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are responsible for\Nmore than yourself now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.25,0:19:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.71,0:19:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Fuyutsuki, I am going to recommend\Na new project starting today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.92,0:19:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I have already proposed it to Chairman Kiel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.39,0:19:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re not going to…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.22,0:19:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.35,0:19:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The path to godhood that none have\Never succeeded in before.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.47,0:19:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The Human Instrumentality Project.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.35,0:19:31.27,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs90\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,347)}YEAR 2008
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.15,0:19:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.56,0:19:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,congratulations on the completion of\Nthe fundamental theory of Magi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.19,0:19:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not exactly a gift to celebrate it with,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.36,0:19:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but my formal admission into Gehirn\Nhas been unofficially approved.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.86,0:19:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I will be working on Project E\Nstarting next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.91,0:19:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Who’s there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.75,0:19:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Technology Development Department,\NRitsuko Akagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.21,0:19:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s my ID.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.92,0:19:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard the command center\Nhad been completed,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.84,0:20:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so I came to see it, but this place is a maze.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.88,0:20:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want the command center,\Nthe Director and Dr. Akagi are there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.81,0:20:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you really sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.81,0:20:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I have no regrets concerning my work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.90,0:20:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Liar! You just can’t forget about Ms. Yui, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.86,0:20:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don’t mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.79,0:20:30.75,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs90\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,347)}YEAR 2010
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.83,0:20:32.16,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\pos(955.909,753.75)}GEOFRONT ARTIFICIAL CANOPY
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.25,0:20:34.21,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs50\pos(955.909,769.417)}LOWER LEVEL 2 DIRECT SUPPORT AREA {\fs40}(FUTURE LOCATION)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.38,0:20:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the headquarters for Gehirn.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.13,0:20:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Director.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.42,0:20:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you bring your child today?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.26,0:20:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but you have a son, if I’m not mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.14,0:20:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn’t Shinji.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.72,0:20:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m taking care of a friend’s daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.35,0:20:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Her name is Rei Ayanami.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.39,0:20:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Rei.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.65,0:20:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This girl reminds me of someone…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.57,0:21:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Yui?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.24,0:21:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All files concerning Rei Ayanami\Nhave been erased already?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.99,0:21:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s blank.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.74,0:21:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.41,0:21:10.62,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs90\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(966.667,800.334)}{\pos(960,785.25)}COMPLETED
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.04,0:21:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Magi Casper, Magi Balthasar,\Nand Magi Melchior.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.21,0:21:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The Magi are the three parts\Nthat make up who I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.17,0:21:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The scientist in me, the mother in me,\Nand the woman in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.01,0:21:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And those three elements will be in\Nconstant conflict with one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.34,0:21:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The three parts of you…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.64,0:21:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing left is to power it up, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.77,0:21:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to go home early today.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.89,0:21:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Misato’s coming back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.35,0:21:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right, I didn’t know she\Nwas a member of Gehirn.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.65,0:21:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe she’s in Germany?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.02,0:21:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, she’s serving in Branch 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.28,0:21:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I suppose it’s a long-distance relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.65,0:21:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard they broke up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.03,0:21:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, and they looked so good together too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.28,0:21:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You can never tell with a man and a woman,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.29,0:21:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,because it’s not logical.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.91,0:21:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That cool attitude of yours\Ncertainly hasn’t changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.87,0:21:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re going to let your own\Nhappiness slip away.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.42,0:22:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is even harder to define.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.42,0:22:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it’s been a long time since\NI’ve gone drinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.67,0:22:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.88,0:22:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.48,0:22:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you want something, Rei?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.65,0:22:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I got lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.28,0:22:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really? Then you want to\Nleave here with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.07,0:22:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.24,0:22:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But you won’t be able to get home\Nby yourself, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.62,0:22:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s none of your business, you old hag.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.33,0:22:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.46,0:22:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I can go home by myself,\Nso leave me alone, you old hag.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.92,0:22:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not nice to call someone an old hag.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.09,0:22:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But you are an old hag, aren’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.26,0:22:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to get mad. You need\Na good scolding from Director Ikari.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.93,0:22:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what the Director calls you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.76,0:22:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.60,0:22:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, “That old hag is pushy,”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.23,0:22:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,or that he, “doesn’t need that old hag anymore.”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.89,0:23:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, “That old hag is pushy,”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.44,0:23:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,or that he, “doesn’t need that old hag anymore.”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.44,0:23:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn’t need that old hag anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.78,0:23:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s what the Director calls you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.29,0:23:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re nothing but a…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.00,0:23:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn’t matter if you die,\Nyou can always be replaced.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.58,0:23:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Rei…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.33,0:23:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The same as me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.47,0:23:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The Human Instrumentality Project Committee,\Nchaired by Kiel Lorenz,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.60,0:23:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,dissolved the research organization,\NGehirn, the next day.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.73,0:23:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And they formed the special duty\Norganization, Nerv,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.90,0:23:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,as the organization that would\Ncarry out all projects.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.31,0:23:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All of us were moved directly into Nerv,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.28,0:23:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,with the exception of one, Dr. Akagi,\Nthe remarkable creator of the Magi System.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.37,0:23:55.28,Matisse Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord2\blur1.5\fs90\3c&H9A9A9A&\pos(960,347)}YEAR 2015
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.45,0:23:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I guess I’ll go.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.13,0:24:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it’s you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.54,0:24:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Long time no see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.59,0:24:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve put the guards outside to sleep for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.55,0:24:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This will cost you your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.68,0:24:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to get closer to the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.51,0:24:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,within myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.18,0:24:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, it looks like they’ll find out
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.31,0:24:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that I diverted the sample of\NAdam to Commander Ikari,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.81,0:24:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,so I have to guard my own interests too,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.98,0:24:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,or various bad things will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.32,0:24:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much for your cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.95,0:24:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it over?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.37,0:24:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the problem has been resolved, so…
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.29,0:24:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.37,0:24:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.54,0:24:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not know.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.89,0:25:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you’re late.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.03,0:25:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m home.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.01,0:25:37.47,Neutral Sign,,0,0,0,,{\frz333.2\c&H000000&\pos(1084.848,224.749)}Play
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.01,0:25:37.47,Neutral Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord5\frz333.2\c&H000000&\3c&H330080&\pos(1579.939,312.333)}Messages
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.48,0:25:48.35,Neutral Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs70\c&H000000&\frz326.9\pos(1043.515,256.749)}Play
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.86,0:25:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Katsuragi, it’s me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.45,0:25:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve probably put you through a lot of trouble
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.78,0:26:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,by the time you’re listening to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.83,0:26:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.33,0:26:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell Ritchan I said I’m sorry too.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.08,0:26:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, since I’ve troubled you so much anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.50,0:26:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s this flower I’ve been growing…
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.92,0:26:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It’d make me happy if you’d water it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.30,0:26:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinji knows where it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.30,0:26:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Katsuragi, the truth is with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.05,0:26:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Go forward without any hesitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.14,0:26:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If I ever get to see you again,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.52,0:26:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll say the words I wasn’t able\Nto say eight years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.69,0:26:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.40,0:26:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Message recorded at 12:02pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.95,0:26:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerk…
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.53,0:26:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re really such a jerk…
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.06,0:27:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Right then, all I could do was\Nrun away from Misato.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.19,0:27:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There was nothing I could do or say.\NI was a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.07,0:27:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It made me realize that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.19,0:27:21.20,TBC Card,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1528.667,770.667)}TO BE CONTINUED
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.75,0:28:52.66,Preview Card,,0,0,0,,PREVIEW
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.33,0:28:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The reality of having lost to Shinji corners\NAsuka into a psychological pitfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.17,0:29:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The futility of panicking only produced\Nweariness and impatience.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.17,0:29:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, the psychological attack\Nfrom an Angel
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.55,0:29:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,delivers the finishing blow to Asuka’s mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.76,0:29:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Asuka loses the means to recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.76,0:29:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The harsh reality tears apart people’s hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.47,0:29:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinji is unable to offer her\Nany words of comfort.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.06,0:29:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time, “At Least, Be Human”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.06,0:29:20.73,ED Title Cards,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\pos(976,756.667)}AT LEAST, BE HUMAN
